SKOS_CONCEPT.definition: Presence of female gonadal tissue or external phenotype.

Presence of both male and female gonadal tissue. (Makris S, Solomon HM, Clark R, Shiota K, Barbellion S, Buschmann J, Ema M, Fujiwara M, Grote K, Hazelden KP, Hew KW, Horimoto M, Ooshima Y, Parkinson M, Wise LD. Terminology of developmental abnormalities in common laboratory mammals (Version 2). Part B. Birth Defects Res B Dev Reprod Toxicol. 2009 Aug;86(4):227-327.)
Cannot distinguish between two or more possible values in the current context. (NCI)
Presence of male gonadal tissue or external phenotype.
